Senior Registered Nurse Infection Control
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/04 07:05:23
Ref. JB3046915
Job Description
The Senior Registered Nurse Infection Control is a member of the clinical team and is responsible for providing leadership of Infection Control provision and services across Mediclinic City Hospital.
Key Outputs:
Coordinate and implement ongoing evaluation of the facility's Infection Prevention and Control policies
Comply with respective state or national accreditation licensing requirements
Form partnerships with multidisciplinary team members to improve Infection Control policies / procedures and ensure these are complied with
Design and plan for infection Control processes and safety systems
Complete Infection Control reports as required and instructed by Hospital and relevant government bodies
Keep abreast of the community disease programs, outbreaks and report and implement actions as per Government regulation
Maintain current knowledge and trends in Infection Control to ensure we are up to date with policies/procedures pertaining to Infection Control
Collect data and maintain data bases for required statistics and reports
Conduct Infection Control audits as indicated
Take part in staff and patient education programs pertaining to Infection Control
Take ownership of the JCIA Infection Control Chapter and standards
Skills
Licensing & Education:
Bachelor of Science or Diploma in Nursing (minimum of 3 years duration) from a recognized Nursing Institute
Proof of valid registration as a Registered Nurse from home country, or an internationally recognized body
Certificate or Diploma in Infection Control (essential)
Skills/Abilities/Experience Required:
Demonstrated ability to deliver a quality Infection Control service throughout the Hospital
Demonstrated ability to work in a multidisciplinary team
Demonstrated commitment to quality improvement for better health outcomes
Fluency in written and spoken English (Arabic language skills are well regarded)
High level of verbal and written communication skills
High level of interpersonal and organizational skills
Demonstrated competence in working autonomously as required
Demonstrated ability to prioritize tasks and meet deadlines
Good computer literacy
Ability to function effectively under pressure
Ability to promote excellence in patient care through mentoring and quality management
Ability to provide leadership to other team members as required
Education
Bachelor of Science or Diploma in Nursing (minimum of 3 years duration)
